EXECUTIVE SUMMARY
-----------------
visionlog is a small Python logging utility that wraps structlog with optional
metadata enrichment (geo-IP, device detection, user identity). The codebase is
minimal (3 source files, ~135 LOC) but is not yet production-ready.

Key blockers are the complete absence of automated tests and CI/CD pipelines,
bare exception handling that silently swallows errors, unused declared
dependencies, and a missing privacy/security model around automatic IP
collection. Several structural and documentation gaps would also need to be
addressed before this library could be safely published and maintained at
production scale.

Overall Production Readiness Score: 2 / 10

